    <h3>What I Do</h3>
    <p>My name is Sam Soffes. I create iPhone, iPad, Mac, and Rails apps at a little company in Dallas, TX called <a href="http://tastefulworks.com/">Tasteful Works</a>. I also <%= link_to "create music", music_url %> and am in constant pursuit of tasting the best burger (ketchup only with pepperjack of course).</p>
    <p>You can find some of <a href="http://github.com/samsoffes" rel="external nofollow">my various open source projects on GitHub</a>.</p>

    <h3>What I've Done</h3>
    <p>I founded <a href="http://tastefulworks.com/trimonix" rel="external nofollow">Trimonix</a> a few years ago and released a <a href="http://tastefulworks.com/countdown-maker" rel="external nofollow">Mac app</a>. I used to work on an iPhone app called <a href="http://youversion.com/iphone" rel="external nofollow">Bible</a> (until version 1.8) that has about 3 million people using it world wide and the web app that powered it, <a href="http://youversion.com" rel="external nofollow">YouVersion.com</a>, at <a href="http://lifechurch.tv" rel="external nofollow">LifeChurch.tv</a>.</p>

    <p>Trimonix is now <a href="http://blog.tastefulworks.com/post/242777197/sam-soffes-and-the-merger-of-trimonix" rel="external nofollow">a part of Tasteful Works</a>. Since the merger, we've released a new Mac app called <a href="http://tastefulworks.com/stage-time" rel="external nofollow">Stage Time</a> over at <a href="http://tastefulworks.com" rel="external nofollow">Tasteful Works</a>.</p>
